column1: The similarity between RhoA effects and thyroid transformation by Ras suggests that RhoA may act as a downstream effector of Ras; in fact, the dominant negative RhoA N19 abolished the down - regulatory effect of Ras V12 over the Tg promoter.

Interestingly, cells transformed by FLT3 and BCR / ABL mutations that confer resistance to small - molecule tyrosine kinase inhibitors were still sensitive to knockdown of PIM - 2, or PIM - 1 and PIM - 2 by RNAi.
A panel of antibodies was used for immunohistochemistry: CD34 / Ki - 67, carbonic anhydrase IX, hypoxia - inducible factor - 1alpha ( HIF - 1alpha) and vascular endothelial growth factor ( VEGF).
